In the last year, the
number of Android users

00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:42.910
who have downloaded a
game doubled compared

00:02:42.910 --> 00:02:46.650
to the previous 12 months.

00:02:46.650 --> 00:02:50.160
And 40% of these
installs are coming

00:02:50.160 --> 00:02:55.180
from emerging markets like
Brazil, India, Indonesia,

00:02:55.180 --> 00:02:56.330
Mexico.

00:02:56.330 --> 00:02:59.220
At Google, we're taking
this very seriously

00:02:59.220 --> 00:03:01.800
and working on a ton
of different things

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:04.800
to help you reach
a global audience.

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:08.880
Today, we will talk about
a few of those things.

00:03:08.880 --> 00:03:12.000
At Play, we are
singularly focused

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.250
on becoming the
premier destination

00:03:14.250 --> 00:03:19.980
for discovery and distribution
of your apps and games.

00:03:19.980 --> 00:03:23.550
Last week, we
announced a Maps API

00:03:23.550 --> 00:03:27.010
that allows you to bring your
game into the real world.

00:03:27.010 --> 00:03:29.280
Super exciting, isn't it?

00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:30.270
I can see nods.

00:03:30.270 --> 00:03:32.760
That's good.

00:03:32.760 --> 00:03:36.690
Today, we'll also announce
that our Google Cloud Platform

00:03:36.690 --> 00:03:38.760
can work across all platforms--

00:03:38.760 --> 00:03:42.420
PC, console, and mobile.

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:45.520
We'll also have sessions
on sharing with you

00:03:45.520 --> 00:03:49.440
the early momentum you're
seeing in ARCore as well as tips

00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:51.950
to get you started.

00:03:51.950 --> 00:03:57.480
Additionally, I want
to share an initiative

00:03:57.480 --> 00:04:02.880
we kicked off last fall that is
personally of interest to me.

00:04:02.880 --> 00:04:05.740
This is about women in gaming.

00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:10.100
After hundreds of millions of
people who play mobile games,

00:04:10.100 --> 00:04:14.310
49% are women.

00:04:14.310 --> 00:04:16.380
But our research
showed that women

00:04:16.380 --> 00:04:20.670
are less likely to identify
themselves as gamers,

00:04:20.670 --> 00:04:23.730
less likely to engage
in gaming communities,

00:04:23.730 --> 00:04:25.530
and less likely
to work in gaming.

00:04:25.530 --> 00:04:28.190
Look around.

00:04:28.190 --> 00:04:34.350
So we kicked off an initiative
called Change the Game,

00:04:34.350 --> 00:04:39.600
where we want to empower and
celebrate women both as players

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:41.330
as well as creators.

00:04:41.330 --> 00:04:43.130
In one of the
sessions today, we'll

00:04:43.130 --> 00:04:45.230
share insights we found
from our research.

00:04:45.230 --> 00:04:46.925
So please take time to attend.

00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:56.410
Now, before I hand off
to the other speakers,

00:04:56.410 --> 00:04:58.650
a few things about today.

00:04:58.650 --> 00:05:00.610
Today's about you.

00:05:00.610 --> 00:05:02.650
We have a whole lot
of sessions, which

00:05:02.650 --> 00:05:06.160
is focused on sharing all
the new tools and techniques

00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:08.060
that we have been working on.

00:05:08.060 --> 00:05:10.330
I want to highlight
three main ones.

00:05:10.330 --> 00:05:12.490
Immediately after
the keynote, we

00:05:12.490 --> 00:05:16.780
will have a session on the
new platforms and innovations.

00:05:16.780 --> 00:05:19.280
After lunch, we
have two sessions.

00:05:19.280 --> 00:05:23.050
One which is focused on really
thinking about how you can make

00:05:23.050 --> 00:05:25.450
your launch successful
and the strategies

00:05:25.450 --> 00:05:30.250
that we can share with you,
and then followed by a session

00:05:30.250 --> 00:05:32.740
on how to think about
post-launch growth

00:05:32.740 --> 00:05:35.240
for your games.

00:05:35.240 --> 00:05:39.190
So I hope you'll stick around.

00:05:39.190 --> 00:05:43.100
You know, this day is about you.

00:05:43.100 --> 00:05:47.890
If you have questions beyond
today please come to our booth

00:05:47.890 --> 00:05:50.740
Wednesday to Friday, where
we'll have more sessions

00:05:50.740 --> 00:05:54.250
and we'll have people who
will be there to answer

00:05:54.250 --> 00:05:55.990
any questions you might have.

00:05:55.990 --> 00:05:59.110
With that, I hand
you over to Mark Vela

00:05:59.110 --> 00:06:02.250
to talk about game discovery
on the Google Play Store.

00:06:02.250 --> 00:06:02.800
Thank you.

00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:05.222
[APPLAUSE]

00:06:05.222 --> 00:06:06.097
MARK VELA: Thank you.

00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:10.580
Thanks so much, Purnima.

00:06:10.580 --> 00:06:11.595
Good morning, everyone.

00:06:11.595 --> 00:06:12.470
My name is Mark Vela.

00:06:12.470 --> 00:06:14.840
I'm the head of games
merchandising for the Americas

00:06:14.840 --> 00:06:16.130
on Google Play.

00:06:16.130 --> 00:06:17.630
And today, I'm
thrilled to walk you

00:06:17.630 --> 00:06:19.213
through some of the
improvements we're

00:06:19.213 --> 00:06:21.980
making to drive games
discovery on Google Play

00:06:21.980 --> 00:06:24.610
as well as the Play Games app.

00:06:24.610 --> 00:06:27.020
Play serves as a discovery
engine for over 2

00:06:27.020 --> 00:06:29.030
billion Android devices.

00:06:29.030 --> 00:06:31.680
And that spans across
smartphones, tablets,

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:34.020
or even your watch, TV, or car.

00:06:34.020 --> 00:06:37.520
And Play is also
expanding beyond Android.

00:06:37.520 --> 00:06:41.630
The catalog is now being
delivered to laptops

00:06:41.630 --> 00:06:43.670
powered by Chrome OS.

00:06:43.670 --> 00:06:45.830
And across all
these form factors,

00:06:45.830 --> 00:06:49.080
Play's mission is to
bring devices to life.

00:06:49.080 --> 00:06:51.560
And I firmly believe it's the
incredible catalog of games

00:06:51.560 --> 00:06:53.840
that you all bring to the
platform that delivers

00:06:53.840 --> 00:06:57.570
the most magical experiences.

00:06:57.570 --> 00:06:59.320
I'm going to touch on
some key areas we're

00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:02.320
focusing our efforts
to enhance discovery.

00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:05.170
Personalization is really the
fundamental building block

00:07:05.170 --> 00:07:06.910
that's made even more
powerful by having

00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:10.060
great content to recommend
and more surfaces to show

00:07:10.060 --> 00:07:12.370
those recommendations.

00:07:12.370 --> 00:07:14.110
On top of that,
we're also seeking

00:07:14.110 --> 00:07:17.650
to create new experiences via
deeper curation, new sections,

00:07:17.650 --> 00:07:18.730
and new content types.

00:07:21.620 --> 00:07:23.870
Now, a lot of the magic
of Play's recommendations

00:07:23.870 --> 00:07:25.484
happen behind the scenes.

00:07:25.484 --> 00:07:26.900
So I want to pull
back the curtain

00:07:26.900 --> 00:07:28.649
and tell you all some
of the changes we've

00:07:28.649 --> 00:07:32.330
made to match the right
content to the right user.

00:07:32.330 --> 00:07:35.300
Late last year, we expanded
our content taxonomy

00:07:35.300 --> 00:07:38.570
to classify games into
thousands of different topics.

00:07:38.570 --> 00:07:40.070
And that feeds our
personalization

00:07:40.070 --> 00:07:41.860
in a couple of ways.

00:07:41.860 --> 00:07:45.020
First, that taxonomy is used
for our recently launched search

00:07:45.020 --> 00:07:46.070
refinements.

00:07:46.070 --> 00:07:48.050
You see this
illustrated on the left.

00:07:48.050 --> 00:07:50.540
Users can now refine
and filter search terms

00:07:50.540 --> 00:07:53.640
to distill down to more
specific content types.

00:07:53.640 --> 00:07:55.670
So in this example,
the user initially

00:07:55.670 --> 00:07:57.710
came in searching
for racing games.

00:07:57.710 --> 00:08:00.020
They were presented with a
number of different filters

00:08:00.020 --> 00:08:03.950
underneath racing games to
distill it down more to match

00:08:03.950 --> 00:08:05.250
what they were looking for.

00:08:05.250 --> 00:08:06.770
They chose motorcycle,
and you can

00:08:06.770 --> 00:08:11.370
see how the content
adjusted to meet that need.

00:08:11.370 --> 00:08:14.070
Second, this expanded
content taxonomy

00:08:14.070 --> 00:08:17.230
also powers the recommendations
on our homepages.

00:08:17.230 --> 00:08:18.990
So we've transitioned
our Recommended

00:08:18.990 --> 00:08:20.130
For You collections.

00:08:20.130 --> 00:08:23.880
They were previously based
on the 17 games categories

00:08:23.880 --> 00:08:25.410
on the store.

00:08:25.410 --> 00:08:29.000
We now can serve over
200 different genre

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:32.049
and subgenre-based
collections to our users.

00:08:32.049 --> 00:08:34.890
So the example that
you see on the right--

00:08:34.890 --> 00:08:37.770
rather than having a broad
collection of sports games,

00:08:37.770 --> 00:08:40.020
we can now dynamically
maintain dozens

00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:42.510
of different, more
specific sports collections

00:08:42.510 --> 00:08:44.460
to meet the users' needs.

00:08:44.460 --> 00:08:46.230
What does this mean
for all of you?

00:08:46.230 --> 00:08:49.710
Ultimately, these
personalized improvements

00:08:49.710 --> 00:08:51.270
give your games
more opportunities

00:08:51.270 --> 00:08:57.020
to surface in more tailored,
relevant collections.

00:08:57.020 --> 00:08:59.482
Now we know how important
games are to our users,

00:08:59.482 --> 00:09:01.190
and I want to share
several changes we've

00:09:01.190 --> 00:09:03.690
made to provide a more engaging
browse experience that's

00:09:03.690 --> 00:09:06.320
specifically tailored to gamers.

00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:08.360
We'll start with navigation.

00:09:08.360 --> 00:09:10.580
As we all know, games are
very different from apps.

00:09:10.580 --> 00:09:12.920
And we've now elevated
games to its own destination

00:09:12.920 --> 00:09:14.480
to reflect this.

00:09:14.480 --> 00:09:18.140
This becomes a foundation for
creating more experiences that

00:09:18.140 --> 00:09:20.330
are unique to games,
such as more immersive

00:09:20.330 --> 00:09:22.460
or recommendations
with video trailers

00:09:22.460 --> 00:09:25.460
and actual screen
shots of gameplay.

00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:27.770
We also want to give
users more control of how

00:09:27.770 --> 00:09:29.600
they explore the catalog.

00:09:29.600 --> 00:09:32.030
One example is a
separate premium section

00:09:32.030 --> 00:09:34.460
that we recently launched
a few months ago.

00:09:34.460 --> 00:09:36.500
This highlights really
the best paid games

00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:38.660
that we have on Play.

00:09:38.660 --> 00:09:41.540
Another great feature that we're
showing on the premium page--

00:09:41.540 --> 00:09:44.660
hopefully most of you have seen
our games on sale collection.

00:09:44.660 --> 00:09:48.260
This features a new
capability we have

00:09:48.260 --> 00:09:49.790
with strikethrough pricing.

00:09:49.790 --> 00:09:51.920
So really conveys
the great value

00:09:51.920 --> 00:09:54.580
that users are getting
with the regular price,

00:09:54.580 --> 00:09:56.330
slash through it, and
then the sale price.

00:09:56.330 --> 00:09:58.850
We've really seen
awesome conversion uplift

00:09:58.850 --> 00:09:59.790
with this new feature.

00:10:03.410 --> 00:10:05.270
Now, within our
recommendations, we also

00:10:05.270 --> 00:10:07.700
want to help users
decide what to install

00:10:07.700 --> 00:10:11.630
by more clearly highlighting
the best of the catalog.

00:10:11.630 --> 00:10:13.889
We've always had editorial
curation at Play,

00:10:13.889 --> 00:10:15.680
but it's sometimes a
little hard for a user

00:10:15.680 --> 00:10:18.860
to differentiate the
personalized recommendations

00:10:18.860 --> 00:10:22.820
from the editorial
curated selections

00:10:22.820 --> 00:10:24.290
and understand why
they should care

00:10:24.290 --> 00:10:27.230
about this game, what really
makes these games unique.

00:10:27.230 --> 00:10:29.630
So one of the major
focuses for this year

00:10:29.630 --> 00:10:31.700
is creating these new
editorial experiences.

00:10:31.700 --> 00:10:34.220
Hopefully many of you
have seen these richer,

00:10:34.220 --> 00:10:36.380
kind of long-form
content articles

00:10:36.380 --> 00:10:39.530
that explain to users what
we love about the games.

00:10:39.530 --> 00:10:43.370
These editor's choice articles
are now live in 17 countries.

00:10:43.370 --> 00:10:46.610
And in addition to a dedicated
section, the editor's choice

00:10:46.610 --> 00:10:49.150
section you can access
from the home page.

00:10:49.150 --> 00:10:51.350
We've also created an
evergreen placement

00:10:51.350 --> 00:10:53.420
on both the home page
and the game's home.

00:10:53.420 --> 00:10:56.480
We continue to add new
articles as we publish them.

00:11:00.450 --> 00:11:03.542
We really strive to celebrate
diverse games on Google Play,

00:11:03.542 --> 00:11:05.750
and we really think a lot
of the game play innovation

00:11:05.750 --> 00:11:08.630
that comes with the platform
comes from our indies.

00:11:08.630 --> 00:11:11.600
So we've put a ton of effort
into amping up our indie games

00:11:11.600 --> 00:11:14.640
featuring via two key areas.

00:11:14.640 --> 00:11:16.700
First, our Indie
Corner destination

00:11:16.700 --> 00:11:19.520
continues to be improved with
more visually exciting ways

00:11:19.520 --> 00:11:21.800
to browse the catalog
and help users discover

00:11:21.800 --> 00:11:24.600
their favorite new indie game.

00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:27.050
And second, we've expanded
our indie games festival

00:11:27.050 --> 00:11:30.530
from its initial roots in San
Francisco a few years ago.

00:11:30.530 --> 00:11:34.700
We're now running contests in
London, South Korea, Japan.

00:11:34.700 --> 00:11:39.140
And most recently, we had our
first ever Latin American Indie

00:11:39.140 --> 00:11:41.990
Games Festival in Sao
Paulo, Brazil, last month.

00:11:41.990 --> 00:11:47.000
We had over 200 nominations
from developers in 17 countries

00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:48.650
and just had
incredible engagements.

00:11:48.650 --> 00:11:50.900
So lots of momentum
behind our indie games

00:11:50.900 --> 00:11:53.060
program, and we're
looking to do more here.

00:11:57.680 --> 00:11:59.630
Discovering new
games is particularly

00:11:59.630 --> 00:12:02.210
important to gamers, and
we're approaching this need

00:12:02.210 --> 00:12:04.010
in a couple of different ways.

00:12:04.010 --> 00:12:06.080
Similar to the premium
page I just showed,

00:12:06.080 --> 00:12:09.920
we've also recently rolled out a
section dedicated to new games.

00:12:09.920 --> 00:12:12.650
Here we seek to really
showcase the latest

00:12:12.650 --> 00:12:16.050
high-quality releases on Play.

00:12:16.050 --> 00:12:18.600
I also want to talk about our
pre-registration program, which

00:12:18.600 --> 00:12:21.780
continues to just drive
incredible results.

00:12:21.780 --> 00:12:23.910
We started our
pre-registration program

00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:26.060
about 2 and 1/2 years ago.

00:12:26.060 --> 00:12:27.630
And during that
time, we've driven

00:12:27.630 --> 00:12:32.190
nearly 200 million registrations
for over 300 participating

00:12:32.190 --> 00:12:33.390
games.

00:12:33.390 --> 00:12:36.930
We're working hard to expose
registration in multiple places

00:12:36.930 --> 00:12:40.620
to build on that momentum
and drive even more results.

00:12:40.620 --> 00:12:42.960
So another thing I
want to highlight

00:12:42.960 --> 00:12:47.820
is a new feature we're testing
out right now with "Westworld"

00:12:47.820 --> 00:12:49.950
called milestone rewards.

00:12:49.950 --> 00:12:52.800
This just kicked off last week
after we worked with a partner

00:12:52.800 --> 00:12:55.320
to announce this,
and what you see

00:12:55.320 --> 00:12:58.020
here is a tiered set
of rewards that users

00:12:58.020 --> 00:13:01.440
can earn as the
community reaches

00:13:01.440 --> 00:13:03.940
these different
registration thresholds.

00:13:03.940 --> 00:13:08.220
So we've already hit the 250,000
pre-registration threshold.

00:13:08.220 --> 00:13:11.730
That unlocks this character
Lawrence for everyone

00:13:11.730 --> 00:13:14.670
who's pre-registered, and
there are three more tiers

00:13:14.670 --> 00:13:20.490
that users can hit as we get to
500,000, 750,000 and a million.

00:13:20.490 --> 00:13:22.840
So really excited
about this feature.

00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:25.740
We think it's just going
to drive a lot of momentum

00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:28.706
to get an entire
community to drive

00:13:28.706 --> 00:13:29.955
towards getting these rewards.

00:13:33.090 --> 00:13:35.280
Now, the store can also do
more than just help users

00:13:35.280 --> 00:13:36.834
find new games to install.

00:13:36.834 --> 00:13:38.250
Should also be a
destination where

00:13:38.250 --> 00:13:40.620
users can find out what's
happening in the games

00:13:40.620 --> 00:13:41.640
they already have.

00:13:41.640 --> 00:13:44.170
We know how it's hard
to sustain engagement.

00:13:44.170 --> 00:13:45.720
We want to help out here.

00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:47.910
So we've started highlighting
major in-game events

00:13:47.910 --> 00:13:49.890
and LiveOps through
store featuring.

00:13:49.890 --> 00:13:52.380
You can see an example
of the FIFA banner

00:13:52.380 --> 00:13:54.870
we did for a squad
building challenge.

00:13:54.870 --> 00:13:57.030
And we've also rolled
out what we're calling

00:13:57.030 --> 00:13:58.770
LiveOps cards on Games home.

00:13:58.770 --> 00:14:01.410
Hopefully many of you
have experienced this.

00:14:01.410 --> 00:14:04.290
These LiveOps cards
highlight exciting events

00:14:04.290 --> 00:14:07.230
happening right now
in those titles,

00:14:07.230 --> 00:14:12.060
whether it's a limited-time
event, discounts, some form

00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:14.550
of new content, a number
of different things

00:14:14.550 --> 00:14:18.240
that we hope will compel users
to come back into the games.

00:14:18.240 --> 00:14:20.430
Lots of exciting
improvements here,

