00:29:28.890 --> 00:29:32.040
and then dive a little deeper
into what our early access

00:29:32.040 --> 00:29:37.440
partners are doing and how
they're succeeding and building

00:29:37.440 --> 00:29:38.160
instant apps.

00:29:42.192 --> 00:29:43.650
And there are three
things I really

00:29:43.650 --> 00:29:46.520
want you to take away
from my talk today.

00:29:46.520 --> 00:29:49.500
So the first is
Google Play Instant

00:29:49.500 --> 00:29:52.860
will transform game discovery.

00:29:52.860 --> 00:29:56.580
Two, that top developers
are already on board

00:29:56.580 --> 00:29:57.870
and succeeding.

00:29:57.870 --> 00:30:03.490
And three, game devs large and
small can build instant apps.

00:30:08.560 --> 00:30:14.080
And it wasn't that long
ago that I was talking to--

00:30:14.080 --> 00:30:16.870
actually, I forgot the
most important part,

00:30:16.870 --> 00:30:20.890
an audience participation
moment that I had planned.

00:30:20.890 --> 00:30:24.490
And let me just give
you some context here.

00:30:24.490 --> 00:30:28.180
So year after year,
we hear that discovery

00:30:28.180 --> 00:30:33.760
persists as one of the biggest
challenges for game developers.

00:30:33.760 --> 00:30:36.110
And so I want to
see a show of hands.

00:30:36.110 --> 00:30:39.190
How many of you in
the audience feel

00:30:39.190 --> 00:30:42.460
that discovery is still one
of your biggest problems

00:30:42.460 --> 00:30:43.772
as the game developer?

00:30:47.630 --> 00:30:50.350
OK, that's most of you.

00:30:50.350 --> 00:30:54.200
And this is a really
meaty problem to solve.

00:30:54.200 --> 00:30:58.390
And so it was one of the
reasons the opportunity to have

00:30:58.390 --> 00:31:01.450
a big impact on this area
that inspired me to join

00:31:01.450 --> 00:31:03.454
this team in the first place.

00:31:03.454 --> 00:31:04.870
And it wasn't that
long ago that I

00:31:04.870 --> 00:31:07.750
was talking to Jon, who I'd
been bothering with "Clash

00:31:07.750 --> 00:31:09.540
Royale" invites for months.

00:31:09.540 --> 00:31:14.140
And he started to
lay out the story

00:31:14.140 --> 00:31:16.360
for bringing Instant
Apps to Games.

00:31:16.360 --> 00:31:18.160
And as he was doing
that, it really

00:31:18.160 --> 00:31:22.660
clicked for me, that by
bringing instant apps to games,

00:31:22.660 --> 00:31:27.550
we have the opportunity to
transform game discovery.

00:31:27.550 --> 00:31:30.520
And we know that
this is possible

00:31:30.520 --> 00:31:34.560
because, in fact, we've
seen this movie before.

00:31:34.560 --> 00:31:39.060
Whenever media becomes
instant, consumption goes up.

00:31:39.060 --> 00:31:42.390
Speed is a huge
competitive advantage.

00:31:42.390 --> 00:31:45.120
We've seen this with music
streaming and movies.

00:31:45.120 --> 00:31:49.350
And before that, Google proved
the transformative impact

00:31:49.350 --> 00:31:52.200
of speed with instant search.

00:31:52.200 --> 00:31:55.050
Music is a particularly
good case study

00:31:55.050 --> 00:31:58.560
on the transformative
power of instant.

00:31:58.560 --> 00:32:01.260
There's a bunch of
studies on the subject,

00:32:01.260 --> 00:32:03.990
and they all pretty
much say the same thing.

00:32:03.990 --> 00:32:08.130
When music became instant,
users played more songs,

00:32:08.130 --> 00:32:12.180
users heard more
unique genres, they

00:32:12.180 --> 00:32:15.360
listened to more unique
artists, and ultimately they

00:32:15.360 --> 00:32:19.470
found better matches
for their unique tastes.

00:32:19.470 --> 00:32:24.020
It transformed how
people discovered music.

00:32:24.020 --> 00:32:28.320
And we believe that instant
can do the same thing for you

00:32:28.320 --> 00:32:30.490
all of you in the audience,
the game developer.

00:32:30.490 --> 00:32:35.280
Imagine users trying more
games, exploring more genres,

00:32:35.280 --> 00:32:39.000
and ultimately finding more
games they love to play.

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:44.760
That could have a transformative
impact on your business.

00:32:44.760 --> 00:32:47.700
And that promise,
that promise is

00:32:47.700 --> 00:32:52.000
why we want to do the
same thing for Games.

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:56.470
We want to turn playing into
the primary way people discover

00:32:56.470 --> 00:32:57.850
and evaluate games.

00:32:57.850 --> 00:33:02.740
No longer will users solely
learn and evaluate games

00:33:02.740 --> 00:33:08.170
on the basis of icons or
text or even screenshots.

00:33:08.170 --> 00:33:12.700
When games are instant, it'll
just be easier to play them.

00:33:12.700 --> 00:33:14.530
And now I'd like to
show you a glimpse

00:33:14.530 --> 00:33:17.650
at the future of game discovery
through the Play Games app.

00:33:25.090 --> 00:33:26.082
All right.

00:33:29.080 --> 00:33:34.800
So imagine that I
have about 10 minutes

00:33:34.800 --> 00:33:36.795
to spend right now,
which I do not.

00:33:36.795 --> 00:33:38.730
But imagine for a second.

00:33:38.730 --> 00:33:41.770
If I had 10 minutes to spend and
I wanted to play a puzzle game

00:33:41.770 --> 00:33:44.010
and my goal is to
head to the store--

00:33:44.010 --> 00:33:47.190
or in this case, the Play Games
app-- and find a cool puzzle

00:33:47.190 --> 00:33:52.590
game, play it, and enjoy it.

00:33:52.590 --> 00:33:53.440
That's the goal.

00:33:53.440 --> 00:33:55.420
The goal is to play the game.

00:33:55.420 --> 00:33:57.390
So we kind of know how
this would go today.

00:33:57.390 --> 00:33:59.370
So you go to a store.

00:33:59.370 --> 00:34:02.970
You would go to the home page.

00:34:02.970 --> 00:34:06.420
You would compare
icons and titles.

00:34:06.420 --> 00:34:08.610
And maybe you'd go
through to the store

00:34:08.610 --> 00:34:10.960
listings of a few of them.

00:34:10.960 --> 00:34:14.310
And at the end of that, you
might install one or two games.

00:34:14.310 --> 00:34:17.400
But instead, now we
fast-forward to the future,

00:34:17.400 --> 00:34:21.480
where you land on a collection
like this, of puzzle games.

00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:25.949
And you can see that there
are a number of them there.

00:34:25.949 --> 00:34:30.239
And instead of going
to the Play Store, when

00:34:30.239 --> 00:34:33.420
we click one of these links,
it will launch directly

00:34:33.420 --> 00:34:36.239
into the Instant experience.

00:34:36.239 --> 00:34:39.409
So this is "Bubble
Witch 3 Saga" from King.

00:34:39.409 --> 00:34:42.320
It loads instantly.

00:34:42.320 --> 00:34:45.949
And in about 30
seconds here, I'm

00:34:45.949 --> 00:34:48.949
going to be able to
complete this entire map.

00:34:48.949 --> 00:34:53.270
I have to save these glorious
owls, which are being shielded

00:34:53.270 --> 00:34:55.610
by these powerful bubbles.

00:34:55.610 --> 00:35:00.100
And I'm able to get a sense
for what this game is like.

00:35:00.100 --> 00:35:03.360
I'm able to compare to games
that I've played before.

00:35:03.360 --> 00:35:06.030
And if I can aim properly,
I will finish this map.

00:35:09.360 --> 00:35:13.870
Think about that-- right into
the game play experience.

00:35:13.870 --> 00:35:17.310
And what's particularly
powerful about this

00:35:17.310 --> 00:35:20.770
is that I can do this again.

00:35:20.770 --> 00:35:22.440
So I'm loading up another game.

00:35:22.440 --> 00:35:24.830
This is "Panda
Pop" from Jam City.

00:35:24.830 --> 00:35:27.000
It's built with Unity.

00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:30.690
And again, jump right into
the gameplay experience.

00:35:30.690 --> 00:35:32.760
And now I have a
good reference point.

00:35:32.760 --> 00:35:35.340
So I'm looking for an
awesome puzzle game.

00:35:35.340 --> 00:35:39.150
I kind of know that I want
to play something like this,

00:35:39.150 --> 00:35:42.870
but this is definitely a
really great way for me

00:35:42.870 --> 00:35:46.410
to understand what I
like about the game,

00:35:46.410 --> 00:35:50.862
understand whether or not it's
worth ultimately installing it.

00:35:50.862 --> 00:35:53.070
And it takes about another
30 seconds to finish this.

00:35:53.070 --> 00:35:56.700
So for the purposes
of brevity, I

00:35:56.700 --> 00:35:58.890
won't go all the way through it.

00:35:58.890 --> 00:36:03.330
But the point is is that
if I had 10 minutes,

00:36:03.330 --> 00:36:07.680
I could have played
10 games or more.

00:36:07.680 --> 00:36:10.890
And because it's instant,
because it's using Google Play

00:36:10.890 --> 00:36:14.220
Instant technology, I don't
have to then go back and remove

00:36:14.220 --> 00:36:15.460
10 games after the fact.

00:36:17.980 --> 00:36:19.270
It's a great way to explore.

00:36:19.270 --> 00:36:22.320
And if we can do this,
if we can do that,

00:36:22.320 --> 00:36:25.830
and we can enable that
kind of experience,

00:36:25.830 --> 00:36:30.060
we'll have fundamentally changed
how people discover games.

00:36:30.060 --> 00:36:33.960
You're playing the game rather
than just reading about it.

00:36:36.570 --> 00:36:39.100
Let's go back to the slides.

00:36:39.100 --> 00:36:41.540
And we've been working with
an amazing set of partners

00:36:41.540 --> 00:36:43.460
in the lead up to today.

00:36:43.460 --> 00:36:47.520
These partners and their games
cover the complete spectrum.

00:36:47.520 --> 00:36:49.880
So we know that whether
you're a giant publisher

00:36:49.880 --> 00:36:53.570
or an indie studio; whether
your games are huge,

00:36:53.570 --> 00:36:57.770
hundreds of megabytes, or
