the opportunity of Google Play

00:43:36.390 --> 00:43:38.280
Instant.

00:43:38.280 --> 00:43:42.590
So the logical next
question is, so how

00:43:42.590 --> 00:43:43.890
do I build an instant app?

00:43:47.540 --> 00:43:49.196
I'm glad you asked.

00:43:49.196 --> 00:43:50.900
[LAUGHTER]

00:43:50.900 --> 00:43:53.720
The short answer is you'll be
able to build your instant app

00:43:53.720 --> 00:43:58.670
the same way you build games
today and with the same tools.

00:43:58.670 --> 00:44:03.500
And there are three
things that we've changed.

00:44:03.500 --> 00:44:07.430
So first, we raised the size
limit to 10 megabytes just

00:44:07.430 --> 00:44:08.750
for games.

00:44:08.750 --> 00:44:10.670
We've enabled the
progressive download

00:44:10.670 --> 00:44:15.320
of executable code and assets
with a split install API.

00:44:15.320 --> 00:44:17.990
And very importantly,
we've added full support

00:44:17.990 --> 00:44:22.070
for native code and are
integrating with game engines.

00:44:22.070 --> 00:44:25.230
And there are two key reasons
why we made these changes.

00:44:25.230 --> 00:44:27.920
First, games are just bigger.

00:44:27.920 --> 00:44:31.580
On average, games are over
twice the size of apps.

00:44:31.580 --> 00:44:33.830
And we've increased the
size limit to 10 megabytes

00:44:33.830 --> 00:44:37.370
because the
expectations of players

00:44:37.370 --> 00:44:40.550
are different for
apps and games.

00:44:40.550 --> 00:44:43.760
And progressive download
gets users into games faster

00:44:43.760 --> 00:44:45.980
because you don't have to
download the whole thing

00:44:45.980 --> 00:44:48.550
at once anymore.

00:44:48.550 --> 00:44:52.930
And second, most games today are
either built with a game engine

00:44:52.930 --> 00:44:58.610
like Unity or Cocos
or native code.

00:44:58.610 --> 00:45:00.610
So what we've done is
enable game developers

00:45:00.610 --> 00:45:03.820
to use the tools they're
already comfortable with

00:45:03.820 --> 00:45:07.170
to build instant apps.

00:45:07.170 --> 00:45:09.960
And this is vitally important,
as this quote from Playtika

00:45:09.960 --> 00:45:11.970
illustrates above,
because it means

00:45:11.970 --> 00:45:16.410
that you can use the same
codebase as your full game

00:45:16.410 --> 00:45:19.250
to build your instant app.

00:45:19.250 --> 00:45:23.170
You can build from
your same codebase.

00:45:23.170 --> 00:45:26.590
That's incredibly powerful.

00:45:26.590 --> 00:45:30.450
And to make that possible
for Unity developers,

00:45:30.450 --> 00:45:32.860
to be honest, probably most
of you in the audience,

00:45:32.860 --> 00:45:35.980
we have to work closely with the
world's most widely used game

00:45:35.980 --> 00:45:37.300
engine, Unity.

00:45:37.300 --> 00:45:41.004
More than 60% of mobile games
on Play are made with Unity,

00:45:41.004 --> 00:45:42.670
and we're excited to
announce that we're

00:45:42.670 --> 00:45:46.700
partnering with Unity to
support Google Play Instant.

00:45:46.700 --> 00:45:48.820
And through this
close collaboration,

00:45:48.820 --> 00:45:50.350
millions of Unity
developers will

00:45:50.350 --> 00:45:53.290
be able to optimize their
current and future games

00:45:53.290 --> 00:45:56.340
for Google Play Instant.

00:45:56.340 --> 00:45:59.220
We're also excited to
announce that Cocos

00:45:59.220 --> 00:46:03.930
is adding instant support
to their IDE Cocos creator.

00:46:03.930 --> 00:46:07.080
But they're going beyond just
adding support in the IDE.

00:46:07.080 --> 00:46:08.550
They're getting
tools to simplify

00:46:08.550 --> 00:46:13.650
the process of trimming down
the game into instant form.

00:46:13.650 --> 00:46:15.180
And we have a treat
for you today.

00:46:15.180 --> 00:46:17.940
Cocos has provided a sneak
preview of their integration

00:46:17.940 --> 00:46:20.250
with instant apps,
and it's awesome.

00:46:20.250 --> 00:46:23.630
Can we roll this video?

00:46:23.630 --> 00:46:24.460
All right.

00:46:24.460 --> 00:46:28.060
So imagine you built a
game in Cocos Creator,

00:46:28.060 --> 00:46:30.880
and you're ready to build
your instant experience.

00:46:30.880 --> 00:46:33.730
You click Android
Instant as the platform,

00:46:33.730 --> 00:46:35.590
and you enter in
a recording mode.

00:46:35.590 --> 00:46:37.780
